properties.WarningTitle: AVOID SMOKE (HAZARD REDUCTION BURN) - Little Mountain (Caloundra) - fire as at  7:57am Thursday,  1 August 2024
properties.CallToAction: AVOID SMOKE (HAZARD REDUCTION BURN)
properties.WarningText:
AVOID SMOKE (HAZARD REDUCTION BURN) - Little Mountain (Caloundra) - fire as at  7:57am Thursday,  1 August 2024 

 

Warning level: ADVICE

 


Warning area: Little Mountain and surrounding areas


 

Smoke is currently affecting Little Mountain and surrounding areas. This is from a hazard reduction burn in the Jill Chamberlain Reserve, Little Mountain. This fire is under control.

 

What you should do:

- Stay inside and close windows and doors.

- Keep respiratory medication close by.

- Avoid driving through smoke if you can.

- Watch out for firefighters working in the area.

- Do not fly drones around the fire. Drones affect air operations.



 

Impacts:

- Smoke can make it hard for some people to breathe.

- Smoke can make it hard to see when you are driving.

- No properties are at risk.



 

Further Information:

- For all warnings, visit the QFES Current Bushfires and Warnings website.

- Follow QFES on Facebook and Twitter.

- For road closures, visit the QLD Traffic website or call 13 19 40.

- Visit the Department of Environment and Science website for live air quality data.

- Find out how to get ready for a bushfire on the QFES website under Prepare - Bushfire.



 

Updates will be issued if needed.

 

This warning is from Queensland Fire and Emergency Services.
